ggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bcz1665702953937.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bcz1665702953937.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bcz1665702953937.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bcz1665702953937\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Naming Rules on ODBC\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bcz1665702953937__p_d54872e1_d54873e1_d54874e1\">The format for index names depends on the value of the <code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"auj1665702731375.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/auj1665702731375.html\" title=\"Specify the syntax of indexes and primary keys.\">key syntax</a>\n</code> connector option. If the data source is not a DOS file, the format is:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bcz1665702953937__p_d54875e1_d54876e1_d54877e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">I_</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">TableName</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">_</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">IndexNumber</var>\n</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bcz1665702953937__li_d25304e1_d25305e1_d25306e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">TableName</var>—name of the Uniface entity\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bcz1665702953937__li_d25307e1_d25308e1_d25309e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">IndexNumber</var>—number of the index\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bcz1665702953937__p_d54878e1_d54879e1_d54880e1\">The following rules apply:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bcz1665702953937__li_d25310e1_d25311e1_d25312e1\">Letters, numbers, dollar signs (<code class=\"ph codeph\">$</code>), and underscores (<code class=\"ph codeph\">_</code>) are allowed, but the first character must be a letter.\n <div class=\"note note note_note\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Uniface accepts only uppercase names in the application model definition.</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bcz1665702953937__li_d25313e1_d25314e1_d25315e1\">If the data source is a DOS file, the format of the index name is <code class=\"ph codeph\">indx</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">nnnn</var>, where <var class=\"keyword varname\">nnnn</var> is a incremental value starting at ‘0001’.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bcz1665702953937__li_d25316e1_d25317e1_d25318e1\">You may not use any of the DBMS reserved words for the names of entities or fields. These reserved words are listed in the DBMS documentation. Table names must also comply with Uniface rules. The same rules apply to field names as for tables.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525980\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525980\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Naming Rules on ODBC Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Naming Rules on ODBC The format for index names depends on the value of the key syntax connector option. If the data source is not a DOS file, the format is: I_ TableName _ IndexNumber TableName —name of the Uniface entity IndexNumber —number of the index The following rules apply: Letters, numbers, dollar signs ( $ ), and underscores ( _ ) are allowed, but the first character must be a letter. Note: Uniface accepts only uppercase names in the application model definition. If the data source is a DOS file, the format of the index name is indx nnnn , where nnnn is a incremental value starting at ‘0001’. You may not use any of the DBMS reserved words for the names of entities or fields. These reserved words are listed in the DBMS documentation. Table names must also comply with Uniface rules. The same rules apply to field names as for tables. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}